## Early game

**Wahiba** on Mars (Dark Sector Survival) is an easy early Salvage source —
Mars is one of Salvage's three signature planets, and this low-level Dark
Sector node is safe to run before a squad is fully geared. Salvage drops from
the enemies you kill, so an endless mission with its higher concentration of
mobs is ideal: a Nekros loot squad and a Resource Drop Booster raise the haul,
and cracking the containers you pass is a bonus on top.

## Mid & late game

**Carme** on Jupiter (Mobile Defense) is the wiki's standout late-game pick,
with a high-throughput Corpus tileset. Salvage is a common enemy drop, so the
fastest way to bank thousands per run is to pair Steel Path enemy density with
a Nekros or Khora loot squad (Desecrate/Pilfer re-roll every kill) and a
Resource Drop Booster. **Elara** (Survival), also on Jupiter, is a solid
endless alternative when you'd rather let a long run pile up enemy kills than
reset short missions.

